review_blob: Nice drinkable pale ale. Great hop aroma with a nice smooth finish. Hard to fault this.
Really liked this, good us style brew, hop forward with a dry finish without being overly bitter.
Pours a hazy golden colour with a citrus aroma. It is quite bitter up front with a dry finish. Fairly solid ipa.
Bottle, really aggressive hop aroma from the glass, citrus, pine, orange peel. Surprisingly balances out with the body to give a great dipa.
Bottle, classic ipa. Nice hop aroma while having a really nice malty backboned body. Really good.
Draft and bottle. Nice orange colour with a big hop aroma and a crisp bitter finish. Nice and smooth mouthfeel.
Bottle, pours black with espresso creme head. Lightish but smooth body, very drinkable.
Nitro from bottle. Pitch black with soft white head. Nice stouty smell. Creamy mouthfeel with a sweet finish.
Draught at craft beer festival. Pours thick and very dark. Coffee and chocolate aroma with the alcohol well hidden. Goes down very smooth. Fantastic.
On draught a few times. Its a great ipa, not as hoppy on aroma as others, has a nice bitter finish.
Probably my favourite beer. The aroma is like nothing else Ive tried, beautiful fruity hop aroma, well balanced and lively on the palate. Just a perfect beer.
Bottle from drinkstore a few months ago. Nice texture to this with a smooth finish, nice dark aroma. Quality beer
Bottle from San Francisco. Nice sweet aroma with a touch of citrus. Looks like a good ipa should, nice moutfeel with good bitterness and carbonation. A fantastic ipa.
Bottle from Bev. Rich, thick, dark apperance. Syrupy mouth feel, like a desert in a glass. Alcohol is apparent but well mellowed.
beer_name: North Coast Old Rasputin Russian Imperial Stout

review_blob: Came back to the brew pub just to try this whilst on vacation on Ryans advice. Super beer, big nose and big flavours. Was worth the extra bit of effort.
Draught & bottle at Russian River. Deservedly ranked as one of the best, nice piney aroma, really drinkable for the ABV. Top class stuff.
Nice head upon pouring, smooth on the palate with a nice dry finish. Really nice stout.
Pours a clear orange with little head. Nose is pine and citrus. Strong orangey taste with a dry bitter finish. Very nice beer, alcohol is well hidden.
Nice orangey, clear colour. Enticing citrus aroma with a fresh crisp taste. Nice bitter finish. Great pale ale.
A light, moderately carbonated red Irish ale. Nice white foamy head, sweet, light bodied taste and a dry finish. The aroma is unremarkable.
Outstanding ipa, nice colour, crisp bitter finish and the hop aroma lingers. One of the elite.
One of my favourite beers, lovely spicy palate where the ginger hits, it appears a little cloudy but the aroma makes up for it. Delicious.
Lovely hazy orange copper colour. Nice bitter taste with big fresh citrus nose. Brilliant ipa.
Bottle from drinkstore. Really nice pale ale, looks beautifull and really refreshing. Nice hoppy nose.
